<br>
The Claw, the TiaChi swords, both have one underwhelming effect - they rob fist crits.  Parry sticks do as well but to a much lesser degree ( as in you end up doing more damage with a parry stick ).<br>
<br>
As most MA's already know we are crit driven in damage.  The Claws low crit amounts interfere with doing max damage as a ma.  There assertion that you subtract 1 fist hit to 1 claw hit is incorrect though.<br>
<br>
You hit with fists 26 times a minute ( if at 1/1 ratio ) with 1 weapon ( also at a 1/1 ratio ) you will hit 34-38 times a minute ( 17 to 18 fist hits and 17 to 18 weapon hits ).  That means you gained roughly 10 attacks, but converted roughly 7 of your normal fist hits into claw hits.  at the high end ( UVC ) that means you converted about 2 Fist crits into sucky claw crits.<br>
<br>
You're best off avoiding the claw.  The down side to the parry stick is the physical init you need to use it to best advantage.  with 1150 physical init you can weild it as a 1/1 at 63.5% agg setting.  Meaning you still have some defense, but are really gaining the most out of the weapon.<br>
<br>
Then again... you should eventually cap physical init any how - a lot of ma's think that 450 physical init and max agg is all you need, at lower levels that's true.  But when mobs start criting for 1 to 1.5 k damage - you really can't afford to fight full agg.  Even high crit chances ( ala LLTS / VE ) aren't really worth the lose of init in the long run because of how high you have to jack your agg up.  <br>
<br>
To recap... Claw = sucks  - waste of a reset point.<br>
<br>
Parry sticks = good! but not to messed with until you have the init to support them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=507.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=507.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=507.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=507.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.threadControl?topicID=507.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=507.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=507.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub83.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table 